TY  - JOUR
T1  - What's the difference? diversity constructs as separation, variety, or disparity in organizations
AU  - Harrison, David A.
AU  - Klein, Katherine J.
Y1  - 2007/10/01
PY  - 2007
DA  - 2007/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2007.26586096
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2007.26586096
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 1199
EP  - 1228
VL  - 32
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Research on organizational diversity, heterogeneity, and related concepts has proliferated in the past decade, but few consistent findings have emerged. We argue that the construct of diversity requires closer examination. We describe three distinctive types of diversity: separation, variety, and disparity. Failure to recognize the meaning, maximum shape, and assumptions underlying each type has held back theory development and yielded ambiguous research conclusions. We present guidelines for conceptualization, measurement, and theory testing, highlighting the special case of demographic diversity
AB  - Research on organizational diversity, heterogeneity, and related concepts has proliferated in the past decade, but few consistent findings have emerged. We argue that the construct of diversity requires closer examination. We describe three distinctive types of diversity: separation, variety, and disparity. Failure to recognize the meaning, maximum shape, and assumptions underlying each type has held back theory development and yielded ambiguous research conclusions. We present guidelines for conceptualization, measurement, and theory testing, highlighting the special case of demographic diversity
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2007.26586096
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.2007.26586096
Y2  - 2026/04/24
